Maybe the balance sheet part is having an effect now with the market zigzagging back into the green, #Dow +47. Most #Fed members are in favor of stopping the balance sheet runoff later this year. Market's been pining for that.

So much for the positive reax by the market after the Fed minutes, #Dow turns lower in a hurry -40. Fed may be pausing rate hikes, but its also worried about the global economy. Maybe bad news is trumping lower rates for the market.
#FedMinutes keep the dovish theme going, with a long list of concerns behind the rate hike pause, including softer business and consumer sentiment and tighter financial conditions. #Dow +73.
